head-line: Man charged after gold bullion and cocaine seizure
outline: Gold bullion worth €1.4m, €460,000 in cash and €210,000 in suspected cocaine were seized.

head-line: Man arrested after €1.4m gold bullion and cocaine seizure
outline: Irish police say a man has been arrested after gold bullion, cocaine and cash are seized in Dublin.

head-line: Ukraine says nine killed in Russia strikes on hospital
outline: Officials say Sumy's hospital was hit in the morning, and was struck again as rescuers were evacuating people.

head-line: Two teenagers die in collision between tractor and car
outline: It happened on the N83 near Levallyroe in County Mayo on Friday evening.

head-line: Austria's far right eyes unprecedented election win
outline: Sunday's election could see Herbert Kickl's party top the polls for the first time.

head-line: Pope says church must be ashamed of Belgium sexual abuse
outline: Belgium's King Philippe levelled direct criticism at the pontiff, saying it had "taken far too long for the cries to be heard and acknowledged".

head-line: Al Fayed’s victims in France call for investigation
outline: One woman says the owner of Harrods and the Paris Ritz ran his companies like a cult or a mafia.

head-line: Man's body discovered at Dublin recycling centre
outline: A post-mortem examination will be carried out to determine the course of the investigation.

head-line: Facebook parent company fined €91m over password storage
outline: An inquiry was launched in April 2019 by the Irish Data Protection Commission.
